In [8]:
df['FundingTemp'] = df['Funding'].str.replace(r'$', '') #Removing '$' symbol and remaining characters in new column FundingTemp

df['FundingPart1'] = df['FundingTemp'].str[:-1] #Slicing all the characters (numeric) except the last non-numeroc character and storing as a separate column

df['FundingPart2'] = df['FundingTemp'].str[-1] #Slicing the last non-numeric character (K,M,B) and storing as a separate column

#Converting each non-numeric character in FundingPart2 column to equivalent numeric values and saving it as int
df['FundingPart2'] = df['FundingPart2'].replace({'K': '1000', 'M': '1000000', 'B': '1000000000'}).astype(int)

df['FundingPart1'] = df['FundingPart1'].astype(float) #Converting FundingPart1 column to float data type

#Multiplying FundingPart1 and FundingPart2 and saving it in new column FundingNum
df['FundingNum'] = df['FundingPart1']*df['FundingPart2']

df['FundingNum'] = df['FundingNum'].astype(int) #Converting FundingNum column to int data type

#Removing unnecessary columns
df.drop('FundingTemp', axis=1, inplace=True)
df.drop('FundingPart1', axis=1, inplace=True)
df.drop('FundingPart2', axis=1, inplace=True)

# Lower whisker or fence can be calculated as First Quartile(Q1)-(1.5*IQR) or the minimum value in the dataset whichever is higher.
IQR = df['FundingNum'].quantile(0.75)-df['FundingNum'].quantile(0.25) #Inter Quartile Range
Min = df['FundingNum'].min() #Minimum value in FundingNum column
Lower_Fence = max(Min, ((df['FundingNum'].quantile(0.25))-1.5*IQR)) #Finding the higher of the two values
print('The value of lower fence is', Lower_Fence, 'Dollars')

The value of lower fence is 5000 Dollars

4. Statistical analysis:¶

  • Is there any significant difference between Funds raised by companies that are still operating vs companies that closed down? Write the null hypothesis and alternative hypothesis. Test for significance and conclusion
In [23]:
#H0(Null Hypothesis) = There is no difference between funds raised by companies that are still operating vs companies that closed down
#HA(Alternate Hypothesis) = There is significant difference between funds raised by companies that are still operating vs companies that closed down
#Two sample independent T test can be used for this
funds_operating = df[df['OperatingState']=='Operating']['FundingNum']
funds_closed = df[df['OperatingState']=='Closed']['FundingNum']
from scipy.stats import ttest_ind
t_statistic, p_value = ttest_ind(funds_operating, funds_closed)
print(t_statistic, p_value)
if p_value < 0.05:    # alpha value is 0.05 or 5%
   print(" We are rejecting null hypothesis. That is, we can say that there is significant difference between funds raised by companies that are still operating vs companies that closed down ")
else:
  print("We fail to reject the null hypothesis. That is, we cannot say that there is significant difference between funds raised by companies that are still operating vs companies that closed down")

Write your hypothesis comparing the proportion of companies that are operating between winners and contestants:¶

  • Write the null hypothesis and alternative hypothesis.
  • Test for significance and conclusion
In [28]:
#H0(Null Hypothesis): The proportions of companies that are operating between winners and contestants are the same
#HA (Alternate Hypothesis): The proportions of companies that are operating between winners and contestants are significantly different
#Proportions_Ztest can be used to test the significance in difference
from statsmodels.stats.proportion import proportions_ztest

stat, pval = proportions_ztest([operating_winners_count, operating_contestant_count] , [winners_count, contestant_count])

if pval < 0.05:
    print(f'With a p-value of {round(pval,4)}, the difference in proportions is significant.That is, we reject the null hypothesis')
else:
    print(f'With a p-value of {round(pval,4)}, the difference in proportions is not significant.That is, we fail to reject the null hypothesis')

With a p-value of 0.8767, the difference in proportions is not significant.That is, we fail to reject the null hypothesis

  • Write and perform your hypothesis along with significance test comparing the funds raised by companies across NY, SF and EU events from 2013 onwards.
In [36]:
#H0(Null Hypothesis): Funds raised by companies across NY, SF and EU events from 2013 onwards are the same
#HA (Alternate Hypothesis): The funds raised by companies across at least any one of NY, SF and EU events from 2013 onwards is significantly different from the others
#We can do One way Annova  test for this hypothesis testing
#We assume that NY does not include NYC, hence we include the condition df['Event'].str.contains('NYC')==False below to exclude NYC
Funds_NY = df[(df['Event'].str.contains('NY'))&(df['Event'].str.contains('NYC')==False)&((df['Event'].str.endswith("2013"))|(df['Event'].str.endswith('2014'))|(df['Event'].str.endswith('2015'))|(df['Event'].str.endswith('2016')))]['FundingNum']
Funds_SF = df[(df['Event'].str.contains('SF'))&((df['Event'].str.endswith("2013"))|(df['Event'].str.endswith('2014'))|(df['Event'].str.endswith('2015'))|(df['Event'].str.endswith('2016')))]['FundingNum']
Funds_EU = df[(df['Event'].str.contains('EU'))&((df['Event'].str.endswith("2013"))|(df['Event'].str.endswith('2014'))|(df['Event'].str.endswith('2015'))|(df['Event'].str.endswith('2016')))]['FundingNum']

from scipy import stats
f , p_value = stats.f_oneway(Funds_NY,Funds_SF,Funds_EU)
print('P Value', p_value)
if p_value < 0.05 :
  print("Reject the Null hypothesis i.e. The funds raised by companies across at least any one of NY, SF and EU events from 2013 onwards is significantly different from the others")
else:
  print("Fail to reject Null hypothesis i.e.There is no significant difference between funds raised by companies across NY, SF and EU events from 2013 onwards")

P Value 0.6328267301763726
Fail to reject Null hypothesis i.e.There is no significant difference between funds raised by companies across NY, SF and EU events from 2013 onwards

5. Write your observations on improvements or suggestions on quality, quantity, variety, velocity, veracity etc. on the data points collected to perform a better data analysis.¶

  • More kinds of data on each startup like net worth, profitability metrics etc. if gathered would help in providing more insights
  • The format of data gathered in Funding column could have been more conventional (like numeric format or other formats that can be easily converted to numeric)
  • The high number of missing values in Funding column and few in Product column makes the dataset seem incomplete
  • Some of the categories under the Result column don't seem to be well separated from each other. Example: 'Finalist' and 'Runner up' seem to overlap with each other.
